{"url": "https://towardsdatascience.com/docker-image-for-nlp-5402c9a9069e", "time": 1682994655.510647, "path": "towardsdatascience.com/docker-image-for-nlp-5402c9a9069e/", "webpage": {"metadata": {"title": "Docker image for NLP. A ready-to-use solution | by Vitaly Davydov | Towards Data Science", "h1": "Docker image for NLP", "description": "NLP is one of the main directions of our work. We do text analysis, chatbot development and information retrieval. Therefore, we regularly use Flair, Natasha, TensorFlow and Pytorch, NLTK, sometimes\u2026"}, "outgoing_paragraph_urls": [{"url": "https://potehalabs.com", "anchor_text": "Poteha Labs", "paragraph_index": 0}, {"url": "http://hub.docker.com/nvidia", "anchor_text": "hub.docker.com/nvidia", "paragraph_index": 3}, {"url": "https://github.com/poteha/docker-nlp", "anchor_text": "source code", "paragraph_index": 4}, {"url": "https://hub.docker.com/r/iwitaly/nlp/", "anchor_text": "Docker hub", "paragraph_index": 4}, {"url": "https://github.com/poteha/docker-nlp/blob/master/README.md", "anchor_text": "versions", "paragraph_index": 4}], "all_paragraphs": ["NLP is one of the main directions of our work at Poteha Labs. We do text analysis, chatbot development and information retrieval. Therefore, we regularly use Flair, Natasha, TensorFlow and Pytorch, NLTK, sometimes encountering languages other than English. Existing solutions are not always suitable for every problem we face: some are difficult to launch, others are too complicated and heavy.", "Consequently, we\u2019ve compiled our own Docker image with all the convenient frameworks for NLP, including deep learning. It suits almost 80% of our tasks and saves time for installing the frameworks.", "Generally, the majority of data science solutions are now deployed in one of the following ways:", "How to deploy GPU in Docker? Firstly, one has to choose a basic image which suits his graphics card particularly (for this, search by tag at hub.docker.com/nvidia). When using GPU everything is anyway inherited from Nvidia images of the required version (for CPU, on the contrary, any convenient image can be used). Then, having inherited from the basic image, one creates his own basic image and runs it. The whole image is going to weigh around 3Gb, however, everything will work fine.", "Having undergone all these difficulties, we, in turn, have created a production Docker image for NLP (source code) which is available and free. A ready image is at our Docker hub. It contains a handful of modern NLP frameworks including those for deep learning. What is inside from the box: torch, flair, spacy, dateparser, pymorphy2, yargy, natasha, nltk, yake (versions). More detailed:", "Four simple steps to install the image:", "With the help of this Docker image, you can save time on deployment by quickly launching it and start with NLP directly. We hope that it will simplify processes at least a little.", "If you have any questions about the installation, please, leave your comments here or contact me directly. Also, feel free to fork the repo and modify the original files.", "Thank you for reading! Please, ask your questions, leave comments and stay tuned!", "Your home for data science. A Medium publication sharing concepts, ideas and codes."], "all_outgoing_urls": [{"url": "https://rsci.app.link/?%24canonical_url=https%3A%2F%2Fmedium.com%2Fp%2F5402c9a9069e&%7Efeature=LoOpenInAppButton&%7Echannel=ShowPostUnderCollection&source=---two_column_layout_nav----------------------------------", "anchor_text": "Open in app"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/m/signin?operation=register&redirect=https%3A%2F%2Ftowardsdatascience.com%2Fdocker-image-for-nlp-5402c9a9069e&source=post_page---two_column_layout_nav-----------------------global_nav-----------", "anchor_text": "Sign up"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/m/signin?operation=login&redirect=https%3A%2F%2Ftowardsdatascience.com%2Fdocker-image-for-nlp-5402c9a9069e&source=post_page---two_column_layout_nav-----------------------